{{Infobox summit | summit_name = Arab League summit | other_titles = | image = Emblem_of_the_Arab_League.svg | caption = [[Arab League]] flag | country = Sudan | venues = | cities = [[Khartoum]] | date = {{Start date|2006|03|28}}&ndash;{{end date|2006|03|30}} | follows = [[2007 Arab League summit]] | precedes = [[2005 Arab League summit]] }}
The '''2006 Arab League Summit''' took place in [[Khartoum]], Sudan, on March 28&ndash;30 2006.<ref>{{cite book | url=https://books.google.com/books?id=ty0uAgAAQBAJ&pg=PT96&lpg=PT96#v=onepage | title=A Comprehensive Dictionary of the Middle East | publisher=Olive Branch Press | author=Hiro, Dilip | year=2013 | isbn=978-1566569040}}</ref> While speakers at the summit called for increased Arab sovereignty and stronger alliances between Arab states, it did not lead to any plans for action to those ends, and Qatari media outlet [[Al-Jazeera]] called it a "nadir" in the history of League summits.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.aljazeera.com/archive/2006/04/2008410131921729408.html | title=A nadir for Arab League summits | publisher=Al-Jazeera | date=3 April 2006 | accessdate=11 May 2017}}</ref>
