[[Image:FONTCezanne.png|thumb|420px|Cézanne typeface]]
'''Cézanne''' is a [[Script_typeface|script]] [[typeface]] based on [[Paul Cézanne]]'s handwriting. The typeface includes alternate characters and swashes. It was created for the [[Philadelphia Museum of Art]] by designers [[Michael Want]] and [[Richard Kegler]] and published by [[P22 type foundry]] in 1996.<ref name="p22">[http://www.p22.com/products/cezanne.html P22 Type Foundry - Cezanne] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080828031417/http://www.p22.com//products/cezanne.html |date=2008-08-28 }}</ref><ref>[http://typophile.com/node/12323? Typophile, ''Richard Kegler'']</ref>

